On Mon, 17 Jan 2000 00:37:16 +0100 (CET), 
Andrea Arcangeli <andrea@suse.de> wrote:
>In our example the per-blockdevice callback should
>convert the dev from hda2 to hda and to add a 15000 wide offset to the
>blocknr.
That assumes a fixed offset and contiguous block mapping.  Is there not
a similar problem with loopback files?  That is, /dev/hda2 block 1000
is /mnt/loop1 block 17.  No guarantee of contiguous mapping there.  Or
has something else already fixed the loopback ambiguity?
